From b67e3a1ddccc52589bb528a14028c66e323927c9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Brian Cain <brian.cain@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 10:11:37 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 02/15] [lld][Hexagon] Fix duplicate R_HEX_JMP_SLOT for
 __tls_get_addr with GD PLT
Content-Type: text/plain; charset="utf-8"
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix an issue where R_HEX_GD_PLT_B22_PCREL and related relocations could
create duplicate R_HEX_JMP_SLOT entries for __tls_get_addr. The bug
occurred because both the generic relocation scanner (via NEEDS_PLT) and
hexagonTLSSymbolUpdate() independently created PLT entries.

The fix has three parts:

1. In RelocScan::process(), prevent the generic scanner from setting
   NEEDS_PLT on the TLS symbol for GD PLT relocations, and prevent
   fromPlt() from converting R_PLT_PC to R_PC for these relocations
   (since they must always go through __tls_get_addr).

2. Add a Hexagon::postScanRelocations() hook that runs early in
   elf::postScanRelocations() to rebind GD PLT relocations to
   __tls_get_addr and set NEEDS_PLT on it. This ensures the PLT entry
   is created before removeUnusedSyntheticSections() runs.

3. Fix hexagonTLSSymbolUpdate() to skip PLT creation if
   postScanRelocations already created the entry (auxIdx != 0).

Also update existing test expectations to reflect the reduced number of
PLT entries (TLS variables no longer get their own spurious PLT entries).
---
